g.text: Vault Antechamber - You are in the antechamber to a grid of rooms that control the door to the vault. Â You notice the number '22' is carved into the orb's pedestal.: orb

Tropical Cave - The cave is a little wider here. Â You find the cobweb-encrusted remains of a small camp, and although you don't suspect the broken pieces of tables and chairs will prove useful to your quest, the fireflies seem to like using the debris as a shelter. Â A passageway leads north and south, and there is an alcove to the east.:
Tropical Cave - Fireflies slowly drift around you and light the tunnel, which seems to get brighter to the south, but dimmer to the north.:
Tropical Cave Alcove - At the back of this alcove, there is a small table, a chair, and a broken lantern. Â It looks like this space was used much more recently than the camp to the west.:

Tropical Cave - You stand at the entrance to a natural cave which looks like it hasn't been visited in quite some time. Â Light pours in through the opening to the south, while fireflies light the path further into the cave to the north.:

Tropical Island - The narrow path slopes downward to the north and leads to the mouth of a small cave. Â A sign nearby reads Â Treasure Vault Access , but different handwriting has crossed this out and written Â Lair of Horrible Monster! Â All non-pirates keep out! .:

Tropical Island - You are on a narrow path between two steep rock faces which look like they have been here for thousands of years. Â Rain trickles down through the vegetation and moss, and through the leaves you can occasionally see a sliver of light hundreds of feet above you where the rock walls end.:

Tropical Island - The embankment of the cove come toegher here to your east and west. Â Between these tall rock faces, there is a narrow, overgrown path leading north. Â You hear waves lapping up on a beach through the dense vegetation to your south.:

Tropical Island - The large trees here seem to be protecting you from the rain. Â As you push through the undergrowth, you can hear birds chirping overhead. Â There is a steep rock face to your west blocking your path.:
Beach - This is a sandy beach in a cove on some tropical island. Â It is raining. Â The ocean is to your south, and heavy foliage is to your north; the beach extends west and east.:
Tropical Island - The east embankment of the cove towers over you. Â It produces a small waterfall here which cascades excitedly into a pool.:

Beach - This is a sandy beach in a cove on some tropical island. Â It is raining. Â To your west is an embankment of the cove which looks too steep to climb. Â The beach extends to the east, and there is dense foliage to the north. Â The ocean to the south seems uninviting.:

Beach - This is a sandy beach in a cove on some tropical island. Â It is raining. Â The steep cove embankment to your east blocks your path, and the ocean waters here look unsafe. Â The beach extends to the west, and there is dense foliage to the north.:
